### Component 2: Updated EnvironmentVariableUtil (Backend)

**Purpose:** Centralized environment variable management with validation

**Location:** `backend/src/modules/common/utils/environment-variable.util.ts`

**Changes:**
```typescript
// Add to IEnvironmentVariableList interface
type IEnvironmentVariableList = {
  // ... existing fields
  googleDriveClaimsFolderName: string; // NEW FIELD
};

// Update getVariables() method
public getVariables(): IEnvironmentVariableList {
  if (this.environmentVariableList) return this.environmentVariableList;

  // Validate and retrieve folder name
  const googleDriveClaimsFolderName = this.configService.getOrThrow(
    'BACKEND_GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLAIMS_FOLDER_NAME',
  );
  const validation = FolderNameValidationUtil.validate(googleDriveClaimsFolderName);
  if (!validation.isValid) {
    throw new Error(
      `Invalid BACKEND_GOOGLE_DRIVE_CLAIMS_FOLDER_NAME: ${validation.errors.join(', ')}. ` +
      `Example valid value: "[staging] Mavericks Claims"`
    );
  }

  this.environmentVariableList = {
    // ... existing fields
    googleDriveClaimsFolderName, // NEW FIELD
  };

  return this.environmentVariableList;
}
```

**Dependencies:**
- `ConfigService` (existing)
- `FolderNameValidationUtil` (new)

**Reuses:** Existing `validateEmailRecipients()` pattern (lines 45-78)

